00:03:10.999 --> 00:03:13.371
to add functionality to your website

00:03:13.664 --> 00:03:16.202
without requiring
a lot of custom coding.

00:03:16.521 --> 00:03:19.416
However,
this also comes with drawbacks

00:03:19.441 --> 00:03:23.773
because a lot of them--
In fact, spoiler alert,

00:03:23.798 --> 00:03:27.969
I haven't found
a page builder that is fully accessible.

00:03:27.994 --> 00:03:30.089
I don't believe
that there is one out there.

00:03:30.114 --> 00:03:32.706
I think it comes
with the nature of the beast

00:03:32.731 --> 00:03:35.151
that we're going to learn to wrangle today.

00:03:36.318 --> 00:03:40.951
But knowing those tools,
they can be helpful,

00:03:40.976 --> 00:03:44.158
and we can choose
what choices to make.

00:03:45.051 --> 00:03:49.248
That takes us into the next thing
we need to cover,

00:03:49.273 --> 00:03:51.281
which is user responsibility.

00:03:51.306 --> 00:03:57.248
Choosing to use a page builder comes
with a lot of responsibility on us,

00:03:57.273 --> 00:04:04.516
the user, the people building these sites,
to choose the best widgets,

00:04:04.541 --> 00:04:07.135
the best modules, the best things

00:04:07.160 --> 00:04:11.191
to make our site
the most inclusive they can be.

00:04:11.216 --> 00:04:14.626
Page builders include
a lot of features

00:04:14.651 --> 00:04:16.545
and things that might look fun,

00:04:16.570 --> 00:04:19.291
but there's an underlying surface there

00:04:19.316 --> 00:04:22.866
that's just not accessible or easy to use.

00:04:23.542 --> 00:04:27.921
Remember that just because
a feature is popular within a page builder,

00:04:27.946 --> 00:04:32.772
or all page builders for that matter,
doesn't mean that it's inclusive.

00:04:33.930 --> 00:04:36.993
Part of the user responsibility
is also ensuring

00:04:37.018 --> 00:04:42.524
that we are doing our proper testing,
so testing on screen readers,

00:04:42.549 --> 00:04:49.579
assistive technology devices,
keyboards, doing manual testing.

00:04:49.604 --> 00:04:54.226
I love tools
such as Wave and Siteimprove

00:04:54.251 --> 00:04:59.927
to help get an overall view
of how our website accessibility is doing,

00:05:00.791 --> 00:05:05.870
but ensuring that we're doing
our manual testing just can't be beat.

00:05:05.895 --> 00:05:08.251
Because we're users.

00:05:08.276 --> 00:05:10.839
We're not computers in this space.

00:05:11.704 --> 00:05:15.973
The first section along
our journey today

00:05:15.998 --> 00:05:19.524
is going to be our page
builder success checklist.

00:05:19.810 --> 00:05:24.467
Whether you have a page builder
that you've been using for a while,

00:05:24.625 --> 00:05:27.371
or you're looking
to just get started with one,

00:05:27.396 --> 00:05:30.570
these are the features
to keep an eye on

00:05:30.595 --> 00:05:35.106
that can give a good indication
of whether your page builder

00:05:35.131 --> 00:05:40.503
is even considering accessibility
in the way that they build things,

00:05:40.528 --> 00:05:44.751
and some do this a little bit
better than others.

00:05:46.015 --> 00:05:51.091
There will be four items
in our checklist to get started,

00:05:51.116 --> 00:05:53.066
and let's get going.

00:05:53.091 --> 00:05:56.559
Our first one is a skip
to content link.

00:05:57.234 --> 00:05:59.963
While this is a simple feature,

00:05:59.988 --> 00:06:03.368
it is often overlooked
by page builders.

00:06:03.393 --> 00:06:05.947
When it would be easy to add it in,

00:06:05.972 --> 00:06:10.729
or at least add a toggle
to where you can turn it on or off,

00:06:10.754 --> 00:06:13.587
please leave the toggle on.

00:06:13.612 --> 00:06:16.906
It is, unfortunately, forgotten.

00:06:17.412 --> 00:06:23.118
A skip to content link
allows a user to be able to

00:06:23.143 --> 00:06:25.158
skip over your navigation

00:06:25.183 --> 00:06:27.713
once they tab into the body of the site,

00:06:27.738 --> 00:06:31.388
and then that way they can get
to the main content.

00:06:31.738 --> 00:06:36.400
As you can imagine,
if you had a big old navigation

00:06:36.425 --> 00:06:40.195
that a user is trying
to navigate through your site

00:06:40.220 --> 00:06:43.036
on a keyboard
or assistive technology,

00:06:43.458 --> 00:06:47.106
they might get frustrated
and even leave

00:06:47.131 --> 00:06:48.331
and not want to deal with it

00:06:48.356 --> 00:06:52.363
if they can't get to the reason
why they're there.

00:06:52.867 --> 00:06:56.308
If this is something
that your page builder is missing,

00:06:56.333 --> 00:07:00.221
it can be easily added
using some custom code.

00:07:00.246 --> 00:07:03.365
I've found that a quick Google search

00:07:03.865 --> 00:07:09.144
will give a good amount of resources
for your specific page builder.

00:07:10.038 --> 00:07:15.817
Here's an example of what a skip
to content link would look like.

00:07:15.842 --> 00:07:20.746
Shout-out to the website
for our event today.

00:07:20.771 --> 00:07:22.861
It may look familiar.

00:07:22.886 --> 00:07:28.803
Again, whenever a user tabs
into the body of your site,

00:07:28.828 --> 00:07:30.361
this is what they will see.

00:07:30.431 --> 00:07:32.097
Along with that,

00:07:32.122 --> 00:07:38.643
just ensuring that this skip to
content link has a good target size on it

00:07:38.668 --> 00:07:40.016
so it's big enough to click,

00:07:40.041 --> 00:07:47.196
and it has a good contrast ratio
so the user can easily tell what it says.

00:07:49.066 --> 00:07:54.986
Moving on into our next checklist items
is our focus outlines.

00:07:55.011 --> 00:08:00.916
Ensuring that items
on our site have proper outlines

00:08:00.941 --> 00:08:05.952
is very important for letting users
that may be on keyboards

00:08:05.977 --> 00:08:09.492
or assistive technologies
know where they're at on the site.

00:08:10.825 --> 00:08:15.524
It's, again, another simple feature that,
for some reason,

00:08:15.549 --> 00:08:17.257
page builders don't bake in.

00:08:17.282 --> 00:08:22.952
It is an easy enough one
to add using CSS.

00:08:22.977 --> 00:08:27.256
Let's take a look
at a better example

00:08:27.281 --> 00:08:30.129
of what a good focus outline
might look like.

00:08:30.577 --> 00:08:34.595
So, I have two images
on the screen here.

00:08:34.620 --> 00:08:38.856
On the top one,
we have three items within a navigation,

00:08:38.881 --> 00:08:44.416
and the second item
is highlighted using a focus outline.

00:08:44.441 --> 00:08:50.096
The user can easily tell that
that's where they are on the site.

00:08:50.121 --> 00:08:52.921
They can easily see it.

00:08:53.041 --> 00:08:57.416
Then the bottom one;
if a user was navigating via keyboard

00:08:58.161 --> 00:09:00.956
or assistive technology,
they wouldn't know-

00:09:01.376 --> 00:09:05.416
they wouldn't be able to tell
that they were on the sponsors link

00:09:05.441 --> 00:09:07.841
or maybe anywhere on the page.

00:09:07.866 --> 00:09:12.041
They would be completely lost,
and this is not great.

00:09:12.241 --> 00:09:16.823
Along with that,
ensuring that your focus outlines

00:09:16.848 --> 00:09:19.415
are also of a good contrast.

00:09:19.440 --> 00:09:24.704
I know a lot of websites,
they have light and dark sections.

00:09:25.331 --> 00:09:32.262
Ensuring that your focus outline
is always a high-contrast color

00:09:32.287 --> 00:09:34.247
is always the way to go.

00:09:34.272 --> 00:09:40.304
I love a good dual-color approach,
so ensuring an outline

00:09:40.329 --> 00:09:44.338
that has maybe both dark
and light colors so that way,

00:09:44.363 --> 00:09:47.041
regardless of the background, 
it's always visible.

00:09:47.367 --> 00:09:51.004
Then also making sure
that it's a good thickness.

00:09:51.038 --> 00:09:56.998
I believe that two pixels is the
recommended thickness for a focus outline.

00:09:59.221 --> 00:10:04.881
As we move along our journey here,
we move into a biggie;

00:10:04.906 --> 00:10:07.401
the proper landmark usage.

00:10:07.728 --> 00:10:13.695
Ensuring that different landmarks are
being properly identified upon our site.

00:10:14.830 --> 00:10:21.484
For example--
Excuse my rough Photoshop skills here.

00:10:21.509 --> 00:10:24.601
It's tougher to find an illustration
of this than you would believe.

00:10:24.952 --> 00:10:29.410
Here is the general,
very simplified version

00:10:29.435 --> 00:10:32.609
of the way the site landmark might look.

00:10:32.917 --> 00:10:38.447
You have your header landmark, and
nested inside that you have a nav landmark.

00:10:38.481 --> 00:10:42.297
Then below that 
we have our main, our footer,

00:10:42.908 --> 00:10:47.839
and another nav element nested
within our footer.

00:10:47.864 --> 00:10:55.515
Your page builder should allow you
to easily specify these things

00:10:55.540 --> 00:10:58.076
if they don't already have them specified.

00:10:58.902 --> 00:11:01.870
Otherwise,
this can be done using custom code,

00:11:01.894 --> 00:11:05.702
but it definitely makes it
a little bit tougher.

00:11:05.801 --> 00:11:11.336
These landmarks ensure that a user
can tell where they are at on a site.

00:11:11.361 --> 00:11:13.961
If you wouldn't be able to see the site,

00:11:13.986 --> 00:11:17.723
you're navigating via assistive technology,
a screen reader,

00:11:18.120 --> 00:11:20.736
it will read these elements aloud,

00:11:20.761 --> 00:11:25.405
and they can even jump to the elements
that they would like to know more about.

00:11:29.371 --> 00:11:34.259
For example, this,
I've taken a screenshot from Elementor.

00:11:34.284 --> 00:11:37.949
What we're seeing here
is Elementor is allowing us

00:11:37.974 --> 00:11:44.921
to adjust the HTML tag to indicate
what landmark we would like this to be.

00:11:45.081 --> 00:11:49.318
In this example,
we have the selected header,

00:11:49.366 --> 00:11:54.255
but it gives you the flexibility
to select whatever landmark

00:11:54.280 --> 00:11:58.481
is best for where you need it to be,

00:11:58.506 --> 00:12:01.571
and ensuring that those
are being used accurately.

00:12:02.208 --> 00:12:05.942
Another thing
that's essential is to ensure

00:12:05.967 --> 00:12:09.091
that these are used
consistently across your site,

00:12:09.116 --> 00:12:15.376
and if you are building websites
for a client or somebody else to use,

00:12:15.401 --> 00:12:23.384
that they are educated
on how to also use landmarks properly,

00:12:23.409 --> 00:12:27.064
or ensure that the website
is set up in such a way

00:12:27.089 --> 00:12:31.477
that they don't really have
to worry about it too, too much.

00:12:32.263 --> 00:12:36.841
Another thing that's important
about these is ensuring

00:12:36.866 --> 00:12:39.380
that everything is properly labeled.

00:12:40.126 --> 00:12:46.917
Going back to our example here
of the setup is within the header,

00:12:46.942 --> 00:12:49.121
we see we have one nav element.

00:12:49.146 --> 00:12:54.185
Let's say we had a nav element
for the primary navigation,

00:12:54.210 --> 00:12:58.169
but within the header we also had
a second one for a secondary navigation.

00:12:58.891 --> 00:13:02.962
Without it being properly labeled
with an ARIA label,

00:13:02.987 --> 00:13:06.375
that could get confusing for a user.

00:13:07.319 --> 00:13:12.955
That brings us
into our last and final checklist item,

00:13:12.980 --> 00:13:16.550
which is a custom
attribute support.

00:13:17.928 --> 00:13:23.230
Custom attributes,
within page builders and in general,

00:13:23.516 --> 00:13:28.457
allow you to be able
to add those different ARIA labels

00:13:28.482 --> 00:13:30.982
to these sections of your website.

00:13:31.007 --> 00:13:34.179
Whenever a user is going through,

00:13:34.204 --> 00:13:37.096
it will read out
that it's a primary navigation

00:13:37.121 --> 00:13:39.296
versus a secondary navigation,

00:13:39.908 --> 00:13:44.816
or it can help clarify phone numbers
that might get jumbled on screen readers.

00:13:44.841 --> 00:13:50.612
Anything to make it clearer
and help reduce frustration for a user,

00:13:50.641 --> 00:13:55.565
just make it an easier world
to navigate the web in.

00:13:56.321 --> 00:14:03.216
These attributes can also
be added using code, JavaScript,

00:14:03.241 --> 00:14:08.093
and stuff like that, if the page builder
doesn't make it easy for you.

00:14:08.118 --> 00:14:12.441
I know that there's a few out there
that are supporting custom attribute support.

00:14:12.561 --> 00:14:17.001
I believe Elementor, Divi,
and maybe Visual Composer.

00:14:17.026 --> 00:14:19.601
I don't know.
That's not a complete list.

00:14:19.626 --> 00:14:23.241
Don't hold me to it,
but it kind of gives you a general guide.

00:14:25.033 --> 00:14:28.551
Here's a few ARIA attribute examples.

00:14:28.948 --> 00:14:30.016
Like I said, a few.

00:14:30.041 --> 00:14:33.305
There's many more,
but these are more of the common ones

00:14:33.330 --> 00:14:37.826
of the aria-label, aria-role,
aria-live, and aria-hidden.

00:14:38.965 --> 00:14:41.456
One thing to watch out
for on page builders

00:14:41.481 --> 00:14:47.561
is I've found that a lot do love
that aria-hidden for some reason.

00:14:47.586 --> 00:14:51.976
That means that if aria-hidden
is added to an element,

00:14:52.001 --> 00:15:00.336
a user will not be able to read that item
with their assistive technology,

00:15:00.749 --> 00:15:03.655
therefore not even knowing that it's there.

00:15:03.688 --> 00:15:07.389
While this item is good
in strategic places,

00:15:07.674 --> 00:15:11.976
I've found it on things
in page builders such as social icons

00:15:12.010 --> 00:15:14.888
that seem pretty essential.

00:15:17.404 --> 00:15:21.877
For some reason,
page builders just love those items.

00:15:22.528 --> 00:15:25.924
Here's an example
within the Elementor editor.

00:15:25.949 --> 00:15:31.213
We have a screenshot here
within the custom attributes section,

00:15:31.656 --> 00:15:35.056
and here I've written out the ARIA label,

00:15:35.081 --> 00:15:39.801
and then it has a pipe
where we add the primary nav label to it.

00:15:40.213 --> 00:15:44.435
Then it will add that
ARIA label to that item

00:15:44.460 --> 00:15:48.872
to make it a little bit easier
for you without custom coding.

00:15:48.897 --> 00:15:54.906
I'm sure that the format of this looks
different across all page builders,

00:15:54.931 --> 00:15:59.136
so read the-- read the documentation
for your page builder

00:15:59.503 --> 00:16:02.342
and find out what is right for you.

00:16:04.071 --> 00:16:05.192
All right.

