00:16:22.321 --> 00:16:26.696
Our red flag list are items
to keep in mind.

00:16:26.721 --> 00:16:29.443
These are accessibility pitfalls.

00:16:29.468 --> 00:16:33.144
Usually, these items
within page builders are not accessible,

00:16:33.564 --> 00:16:36.216
so we need to keep
a very close eye on them,

00:16:36.241 --> 00:16:39.771
and in some cases,
we'll avoid them completely.

00:16:40.455 --> 00:16:41.835
Don't worry, though.

00:16:41.909 --> 00:16:49.029
I'll offer some good, more accessible
alternatives to those items as well.

00:16:50.599 --> 00:16:57.314
Bringing us in strong, waving us in with
that red flag are interactive elements.

00:16:57.339 --> 00:17:02.736
These are items such as flip boxes,
interactive circles, flip carousels.

00:17:03.311 --> 00:17:05.601
I mean, honestly, anything that says flip

00:17:05.626 --> 00:17:08.601
or interactive within
a page builder, I just say-

00:17:08.721 --> 00:17:10.081
[chuckles] I usually nope out of.

00:17:10.738 --> 00:17:18.401
These kinds of items like
to take valuable content and hide them

00:17:18.426 --> 00:17:22.336
from the user or force them
to interact with it

00:17:22.361 --> 00:17:24.256
in order to be able to see it.

00:17:24.609 --> 00:17:29.209
This could be in the form
of a hover or a focus

00:17:29.583 --> 00:17:33.353
that the user has to perform
in order to see this content

00:17:33.378 --> 00:17:36.869
because it's hidden behind
a box or an element.

00:17:38.605 --> 00:17:43.900
These are definitely
an avoid completely in my list.

00:17:43.925 --> 00:17:48.756
They are excluding users,
and they're just plain bad.

